I log in tonight and *gasp* FV was one of the least populated servers!<br>
So I'm figuring &quot;great, maybe I even stand a chance at getting Noclin's femur!&quot;<br>
Ahhh, not to be I'm afraid. The Paineel zone had 28 people in it, most of them in the newbie gardens.<br>
Now, this would not normally cause me frustration.<br>
What DID cause me frustration is running around conning foreigners to Paineel and coming up red every time with ONE exception.<br>
I'm level 3... so I'm wondering what in the hell lvl 6 or up players might be doing in a newbie zone designed to get people to 4th level.<br>
And what do you all figure this reason might be?<br>
That's right, farming bone chips (or attempting, I dunno if the TLC came into play or not.. I'd say not because these people still ran around killing skellies).<br>
So while there is a city full of necros who can both:<br>
a) really use the bone chips<br>
and<br>
b) honestly use the xp too<br>
you would have had a rough time getting them.<br>
So, being the nice guy I am, what did I do?<br>
I gave them hell through tells. Asking them why they were here, and being disappointed with the one I got ripping into them for stealing spawns from people who could use it just as an attempt to make quick cash because they were too lazy to actually PLAY.<br>
Now, am I in the right? No, but I don't really care. There's no good excuse for a lvl 6 and above to be in a zone for lvls 1-4 trying to make quick money at the expense of others.<br>
I don't even expect to see this on other servers (and quite honestly, on Vazaelle, I HAVEN'T.. maybe because people there have enough money to buy what they need).<br>
This sort of behavior makes me wonder, even with all the great talks I've had on FV (which you can also have on the other servers if you actually start the exchange yourself), why I should give up playing a main I've worked fairly hard on to play here.<br>
